    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, intentional? I'm looking at the approved structural blueprints right now, and I don't see any provision for a 2-inch deviation due to soil settling. Usually, any settlement allowance would be explicitly noted in the site plan or the engineering change orders. Are you sure there isn't a mistake in your documentation, or perhaps an error in the pour itself? I'd hate to have to halt work to verify this with the lead engineer if there's an unapproved deviation.",
